rance\", \"score\": 0.9142432168799417, \"rank\": 0.08215526313984556, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Benoit Tessier/File Photo    PublishedJan 12, 2024, 09:46 PM  UpdatedJan 12, 2024, 09:46 PM  LONDON  -     Anheuser-Busch InBev will be an official sponsor for three Olympic Games starting with the Paris 2024 summer event this year, the brewer said on Friday, naming its alcohol-free Corona Cero as the official beer of the Games.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 410, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9807423079562896, \"rank\": 0.019609037561239325, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 608, \"end\": 618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.979545254218182e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The maker of Budweiser, Corona and Stella Artois will be a Worldwide Olympic Partner, the highest level of Olympic sponsorship, for this year's Games as well as the 2026 Winter Olympics in Milan and the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\", \"score\": 0.9520064332462163, \"rank\": 0.0504130697836387, \"text\": \"Budweiser\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\"}, {\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\", \"score\": 0.9999973841088485, \"rank\": 2.1199773635673712e-06, \"text\": \"Corona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\"}, {\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Artois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stella Artois\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Artois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Artois\"}, {\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.9975448782224599, \"rank\": 0.0024611640943453415, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 962, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999781441604, \"rank\": 2.1443304118833686e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AB InBev CEO Michel Doukeris said: \\\"We are proud to be the first beer sponsor for the Olympics at the Worldwide Olympic Partner level.\\\"\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 989, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Doukeris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michel Doukeris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Doukeris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Doukeris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company declined to disclose the value of the deal.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As drinks companies globally try to adapt to consumers curbing their alcohol consumption, AB InBev said the spotlighting of Corona Cero at the Olympics is part of its efforts towards \\\"responsible alcohol consumption and moderation worldwide\\\".\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"score\": 0.9997315750097934, \"rank\": 0.0002684970614461838, \"text\": \"InBev\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\"}, {\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\", \"score\": 0.9999973841088485, \"rank\": 2.1199773635673712e-06, \"text\": \"Corona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Corona\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not the first time an alcohol-free beer has sponsored a sporting event: Diageo promoted Guinness 0.0 at last year's Six Nations rugby tournament.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diageo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diageo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diageo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diageo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But booze is still central to many events.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2022 soccer World Cup in Qatar, some fans were disappointed by a last-minute ban on the sale of alcohol in stadiums, hurting Budweiser.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999998210294212, \"rank\": 1.7478899002062584e-07, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\", \"score\": 0.9520064332462163, \"rank\": 0.0504130697836387, \"text\": \"Budweiser\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anheuser-Busch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The beer of the LA Games, Michelob ULTRA, does contain alcohol but is a \\\"light\\\" beer with a 3.5% alcohol content, AB InBev said.\", \"from\": 1753, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"score\": 0.9997315750097934, \"rank\": 0.0002684970614461838, \"text\": \"InBev\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luxury giant LVMH is also a Paris Olympics sponsor, signing a deal last year expected to cost around 150 million euros that will see Moet Hennessy champagnes and spirits be provided as part of hospitality programmes at the Games.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1896, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.743140198375574e-30, \"text\": \"LVMH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\"}, {\"begin\": 1911, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2016, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moet Hennessy\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AB InBev joins global companies including AirBnb, Alibaba, Coca-Cola, P&amp;G, Toyota, and Visa as top Olympic sponsors.\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2117, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"score\": 0.9997315750097934, \"rank\": 0.0002684970614461838, \"text\": \"InBev\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/InBev\"}, {\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AirBnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}, {\"begin\": 2164, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alibaba_Group\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 1.0953591737059232e-12, \"text\": \"Alibaba\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alibaba_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alibaba_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.999999555588473, \"rank\": 4.4441163822327736e-07, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}, {\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.43368296357091e-14, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://db